1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:01,760
CHAPTER ONE

2
00:00:02,320 --> 00:00:03,600
On board the Parvina

3
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:09,920
Leaning on the rail at the stern of the 
cruise ship Parvina, sipping his champagne,  

4
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:17,280
Eddie Munro looked out across the water and into 
the darkness. There was a warm, gentle breeze,  

5
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:23,200
and the sea was calm except for the dizzy trail of 
water churned up by the ship's angry propellers.  

6
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:29,840
It was a beautiful evening and there was no 
one else on deck. Eddie liked it that way. 

7
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:34,000
He looked down at his watch, 
which showed 10.31 p.m.,  

8
00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:37,200
and the ship was already 
half a mile from the harbour.  

9
00:00:39,040 --> 00:00:44,800
He was amazed that such a huge cruise ship could 
move so fast - he was amazed it stayed afloat at  

10
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:51,280
all! He watched St Thomas island getting further 
and further away. He stared at the silhouette of  

11
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:58,560
the island, at its faint black shapes of hills 
rising up into the night sky. Eddie smiled to  

12
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:03,520
himself as he noticed he could no longer see 
where the lights ended and the stars began. 

13
00:01:05,280 --> 00:01:10,400
He finished his champagne and, for good 
luck, threw the glass far out into the sea.  

14
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:16,640
He never heard it drop. He couldn't see much 
at all in the warm Caribbean darkness, but he  

15
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:22,400
noticed for the first time how high up he was. 
The sea was a long, long way down, he thought. 

16
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:30,480
At this point his wife, Lynn, came out looking 
for him, wearing her long black evening dress  

17
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:36,480
and the silk purple scarf she had bought on the 
excursion earlier in the day. Her hair was dark  

18
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:42,080
and short with plum-coloured highlights.
He turned to put his arm around her as she  

19
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:46,880
joined him. He noticed her perfume, 
a powerful and luxurious scent. 

20
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:55,040
"Hello," he said, turning round. "You smell 
nice. And you look lovely. Are you married?" 

21
00:01:56,160 --> 00:02:00,800
"Yes, thank you. To a very wealthy 
man, so you have no chance,"  

22
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:03,840
she said, smiling.
"Ah. But so am I." 

23
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:12,480
"Ah, so you're married to a wealthy man, are you?"
"I mean I'm wealthy. Very rich, in fact." 

24
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:21,200
"Well aren't you the lucky one," Lynn said.
"Yes, so if you're lucky, I might buy you dinner,"  

25
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:24,080
said Eddie, turning back to 
look out to sea once more. 

26
00:02:25,040 --> 00:02:31,680
"Well, lucky me. How can I refuse such charm?" 
She looked at him and took hold of his hand.  

27
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:37,760
She smiled and stared out into the night, too, 
to the island which was now even further away. 

28
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:42,720
"I thought I'd find you out here," she said. "How  

29
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:44,960
many glasses have you thrown 
into the sea this evening?" 

30
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:47,760
"Only two," he said.
"Eddie!" 

31
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:51,600
"It's good luck."
"No, it isn't. Not  

32
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:56,960
if you're a fish and you get hit by a glass."
"The fish might like it. It's probably quite  

33
00:02:56,960 --> 00:03:01,760
boring being a fish. The sudden arrival of a 
champagne glass might brighten up your life." 

34
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:07,600
"Or end it," she said.
"It's fun," said Eddie. "You should try it." 

35
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:11,120
"I think I've had enough 
champagne," his wife said. 

36
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:18,320
"I love the way the glass disappears the minute 
it leaves my hand, and the sea eats it up. You  

37
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:22,640
can't see it falling and you can't hear it 
hit the water. But you know it's landed,  

38
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:28,480
dived in and sunk to the bottom. Imagine 
- a tiny glass holding a giant ocean." 

39
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:36,240
"You think too much," she said, moving away 
and pulling him with her. "Why don't you come  

40
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:40,240
back inside? They're serving coffee and 
I think there's going to be some jazz." 

41
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:43,600
"All right," he said. "Just a few more minutes." 

42
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:49,600
"We have two more weeks on this cruise, Eddie. 
You have plenty of time to take it all in." 

43
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:54,720
"It's incredible, though, isn't 
it? So beautiful. It's perfect." 

44
00:03:55,840 --> 00:04:00,960
Lynn laughed. "It's completely black. 
I can't see anything in the dark." 

45
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:06,240
"I know. But it's all out there. 
The blue sea, the white sand,  

46
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:09,840
the palm trees, the boats..."
"The champagne glasses..." 

47
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:17,920
"Very funny," said Eddie. Then he pointed to the 
horizon. "Look over there at the dots of light. Do  

48
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:25,360
you think they're lights on the island or stars?"
Lynn looked hard into the night and gave it some  

49
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:30,720
thought. "Erm... lights."
"But you're not sure." 

50
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:37,360
"I am sure. I'm always sure."
"Hmm," he said. "How is that?" 

51
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:43,040
"Because I'm always right," she said, smiling.
"Oh really?" 

52
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:47,360
"Of course. I was right about setting 
up your own business, wasn't I?" 

53
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:50,720
"Yes."
"And I was right about  

54
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:55,840
selling the business off this year for twenty 
million - only sixteen years after starting." 

55
00:04:56,560 --> 00:05:00,160
"Possibly," he teased. He 
wouldn't give in so easily. 

56
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:06,400
"And I was right to let you take me on this 
cruise to relax and celebrate in style." 

57
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:12,000
"Oh, I see. How generous."
"Just think. You don't have to  

58
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:17,760
work ever again. You're a millionaire, 
Mr Edward Munro. How does that sound?" 

59
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:25,120
"Lucky me," he said proudly.
"Yes, lucky you. Lucky us. Now  

60
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:29,680
come inside before we lose all our money 
paying for missing champagne glasses." 

61
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:38,400
Back inside, the dining room was full of people. 
It was hot, but the lighting made it welcoming  

62
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:44,320
and comfortable. In the time Eddie had been 
outside, a space had been cleared for dancing and  

63
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:50,800
a few couples were already on their feet. In the 
corner, four musicians, three men and one woman,  

64
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:56,560
were playing a song Eddie knew well, but he 
couldn't recall its name. The singer was wearing a  

65
00:05:56,560 --> 00:06:02,800
navy blue cocktail dress, and the men were wearing 
tuxedos, black ties and formal dinner suits. 

66
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:09,280
Eddie noticed how young the woman looked. Too 
young to have known the tune when it first  

67
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:15,440
appeared, Eddie thought, but her voice was strong 
and clear. And she seemed to believe in the words,  

68
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:21,760
at least. How old was she? Twenty-five? 
Twenty-six? Imagine singing on a cruise  

69
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:27,120
ship in your twenties! What a life! 
The fun, the parties, the people.  

70
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:31,200
The places to go and things to see 
- before your life had even started. 

71
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:38,320
It seems so easy now, Eddie thought. His twenties 
had been very different. And his thirties.  

72
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:45,120
Eddie tried not to think about his own past. Now 
was all that mattered. The past was the past.  

73
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:51,200
'What doesn't kill you makes you stronger,' 
Clive, his business partner, always said. 'No  

74
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:56,560
such thing as luck,' he once said, 'it's simply 
the moment when preparation meets opportunity.' 

75
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:01,840
By now, Eddie was sitting back at 
his table and next to his wife.  

76
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:07,760
She was watching the band and tapping the table. 
She smiled at the other passengers opposite her,  

77
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:10,560
who smiled back, relaxed and enjoying the moment.  

78
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:18,400
Eddie looked at his watch. It was almost 11 p.m., 
but he wasn't tired. Quite the opposite. He felt  

79
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:23,520
relaxed and energized. He'd always been 
an evening person, never a morning person. 

80
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:29,360
He looked around at the giant lounge with 
its circular tables and well-dressed diners,  

81
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:34,960
and the perfect white tablecloths. The waiters 
and waitresses in their smart uniforms moved  

82
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:40,000
smoothly in and out of the room, and Eddie's 
eyes followed them as they carried plates  

83
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:45,280
and coffee and cakes and trays around the 
tables, along the aisles and past the bar. 

84
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:51,520
Eddie watched the barman throwing ice cubes 
and cocktail shakers in the air and juggling  

85
00:07:51,520 --> 00:07:57,840
them as he made the drinks in acrobatic style. 
He was confident and polished, and also young.  

86
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:03,200
Possibly the same age as the singer. 
Why was everyone so young these days?  

87
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:08,080
Where were all the cruise ship jobs when 
Eddie was trying to get started in life?  

88
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:12,320
Why hadn't he thought of working 
on a ship in the Caribbean? 

89
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:19,040
He found himself staring at the bar in the 
distance. He was no longer thinking of anything  

90
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:24,160
in particular. He was simply listening to the 
sounds of jazz and the noise of a few hundred  

91
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:28,160
people talking and laughing.
And that was when he saw him. 

92
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:34,160
That was the moment when he saw Dominic 
for the first time in many, many years.  

93
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:39,840
The man was sitting at the bar, leaning 
forward and smoking a large cigar.  

94
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:47,120
He was older now, clearly, and his hair was very 
grey, but Eddie had no doubt that it was him.  

95
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:50,880
He couldn't believe that awful 
man was here on the ship. 

96
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:57,280
And then everything was different.
Nothing was the same. All was spoiled. 

97
00:08:58,160 --> 00:09:01,120
Just like before.
 
CHAPTER TWO

98
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:02,880
Argument with Dominic

99
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:10,640
"You know your problem, Eddie?" said Dominic 
Stephens in his office. "You're too hands-on."  

100
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:18,560
He leaned back in his large, leather chair behind 
his glass desk. He seldom made eye contact. His  

101
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:24,480
shoulders looked tense and his neck was hidden.
"I don't understand," said Eddie. "How can that  

102
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:30,720
be a problem? The team really appreciates my style 
and the customers love it. It's what I do best.  

103
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:36,640
It's why I was brought here in the first place."
"Oh, really?" said Dominic, clearly unimpressed. 

104
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:41,600
"I know for a fact that Ann and Gary 
didn't want an executive to run things.  

105
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:48,240
They wanted someone with practical experience, 
and drive - and lots of it. They said dull and  

106
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:53,680
uninspiring executives and managers have 
come and gone and there's been no direction,  

107
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:59,520
no feeling for the business. No passion."
"And you have passion?" said Dominic. 

108
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:04,960
"Yes. Do you?"
"This isn't about me, Eddie. It's about you,  

109
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:09,360
and it takes more than passion to do 
this job. You need to be a leader." 

110
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:16,320
"I am a leader," replied Eddie. "I've done it 
for years. My track record speaks for itself." 

111
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:22,320
"Well, you can't do it all by yourself."
"I'm not trying to do it all by myself,  

112
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:28,080
Dominic. I'm building a team. I'm training new 
people. Resources are limited. It takes time." 

113
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:33,600
"We don't have time, Eddie."
What did Dominic Stephens know  

114
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:39,760
about passion or time? wondered Eddie. The only 
passion he seemed to have was being in charge.  

115
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:46,080
And golf. He seemed to have a lot of time 
for that. He even kept his clubs in the  

116
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:52,480
corner of his office. And today was Thursday. 
On Thursdays he always left early to play golf  

117
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:57,920
and he didn't even try to hide it.
Eddie was so angry his mouth was dry.  

118
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:03,440
"I don't know why you have a problem with 
me, Dominic. There's nothing wrong with my  

119
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:06,880
performance. Quite the opposite in fact."
"Oh, really?" 

120
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:14,000
"Yes. When I joined Fenton's, they were only 
producing software for small businesses in the UK.  

121
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:18,080
They had some accounting packages 
and sales and marketing databases,  

122
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:23,840
but not much else. I was brought in to expand 
the business and build exports, and that is  

123
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:30,160
exactly what I have done. I brought in some very 
talented people to develop our products, and we  

124
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:35,840
now offer some unique and very powerful programs 
used by the biggest and best companies globally.  

125
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:42,240
When I proposed and won the Moscow account, 
you said it couldn't be done, and now we  

126
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:49,040
supply the entire Russian region."
"Erm, excuse me, Mr Passion. I  

127
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:54,160
won the Moscow contract for you," said 
Dominic, pointing firmly at his own chest. 

128
00:11:55,200 --> 00:12:02,320
Eddie could not believe his ears. This was so 
unfair. Rage filled his whole mind and body.  

129
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:08,560
"You did not win that contract. You knew some of 
the people in the Russian state department there,  

130
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:14,560
that's all. I spent most of last year - and the 
year before - going to Russia and working long,  

131
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:19,280
long hours to build a business plan that would 
work. Don't take the credit away from me,  

132
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:24,480
Dominic. Without me, this company could 
never have won such a high-profile project." 

133
00:12:25,280 --> 00:12:30,320
"Well, I still haven't seen the final numbers, 
and I still haven't seen the new business plan,"  

134
00:12:30,880 --> 00:12:36,560
Dominic said, throwing his arms around.
"Yes, you have. I've kept you informed  

135
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:42,640
the whole time with numerous emails."
"Oh, emails, emails! I don't have time  

136
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:48,080
for emails. I get about three hundred a day. 
How on earth can I keep up with all that?" 

137
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:54,240
Well, it would help if you didn't play so much 
golf, Eddie wanted to say. It would help if you  

138
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:58,560
let me do my job and didn't interfere. It 
would help if you weren't so aggressive.  

139
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:06,000
Instead, he tried to remain diplomatic and 
said, "Well, if you don't read my emails,  

140
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:10,320
how can we communicate?"
"Simple. Pick up the phone." 

141
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:17,680
He made it sound so easy. This was ridiculous. 
"I do call you, Dominic. You're never there.  

142
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:22,560
I leave messages but you don't call 
back. When we do get time to meet,  

143
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:28,320
I don't think you're really listening."
"I'm always listening to you, Eddie," said  

144
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:36,800
Dominic in a weary voice. "Because you talk so 
much, that's all you ever do. Talk, talk, talk." 

145
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:43,040
"You're making personal comments, and that is 
not professional. I talk because I'm passionate.  

146
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:48,320
And I deliver. If I say I'll do something, I 
do it, and within budget, and you know it." 

147
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:54,880
"You were not on budget. Last year 
you went over budget by 25,000 pounds" 

148
00:13:55,920 --> 00:14:01,600
Not this again. Eddie was so tired of 
the same story. "I can account for every  

149
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:06,480
penny my department spent. No one seems to 
know what happened to that 25,000 pounds." 

150
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:11,840
Dominic looked at him accusingly.
"Don't look at me like that,"  

151
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:14,000
said Eddie.
"Like what?" 

152
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:22,080
"Look, the way I see it..." Eddie began, but again 
he was cut off in mid-sentence. Dominic always  

153
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:29,280
interrupted everyone. He was like a spoilt child.
And so the situation was impossible. Eddie  

154
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:33,680
simply wanted to leave. He could no 
longer focus. He could never win. 

155
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:41,040
Eddie came out of the office. His whole body was 
trembling, and he tried very hard not to slam the  

156
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:47,920
door, scream or break something. He realized he 
was too angry and too upset to go back to the team  

157
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:52,880
or finish his work. He decided to slip 
out of the office for ten minutes,  

158
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:59,520
just to calm down. He would have a coffee. 
Or call Lynn. Come on, Ed, he told himself.  

159
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:02,960
Get things in perspective. It's only a job. 

160
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:09,920
He was almost at reception and the main door, when 
Clive passed him on the way to the photocopier.  

161
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:13,440
"Ed, what's wrong?" he asked, 
stopping in the corridor. 

162
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:19,520
Eddie couldn't speak. He was afraid to say 
anything, as he didn't know what might come out.  

163
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:25,120
His face was red and tears were 
stinging his eyes. He looked down,  

164
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:30,720
ignored Clive and walked out of the door into 
the street and towards the local cafe.
 
 

165
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:32,560
CHAPTER THREE

166
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,320
Someone from the past

167
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:40,640
"You all right, Eddie?" asked Lynn, who 
had noticed Eddie staring at the bar.  

168
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:49,360
Eddie took a moment and then said, "Yes, fine. 
Why?" But he was still lost in thought. He wasn't  

169
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:55,520
sure if the ship was moving or if he was dizzy.
"You look so serious. Come on, let's dance." 

170
00:15:56,880 --> 00:16:04,560
He was still staring at the bar. The man was still 
there. It was Dominic. Sitting at the bar barely  

171
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:12,000
fifty meters away, drinking and smoking. As simple 
as that. Was the world so small? thought Eddie.  

172
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:19,760
Couldn't it be a bit bigger? Why here? Why now? 
After all this time. Why on this ship? A familiar  

173
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:23,920
sickness in his stomach returned.
"Well, don't get too excited,  

174
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:29,600
will you?" Eddie heard his wife say.
"Sorry?" he said, turning his attention to Lynn. 

175
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:36,480
"A dance! Can we dance?" Lynn said impatiently.
"Yes, sure. Sorry." 

176
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:42,400
They both got up and walked to the dance 
floor. They held each other and danced  

177
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:46,720
slowly for the final verse of yet another 
song whose name Eddie couldn't remember. 

178
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:53,280
Turning in the dance, Eddie was pleased that 
Lynn was there with him as he tried to take in  

179
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:58,800
the fact that he was now staring at the distant 
shape of Dominic Stephens, on the far side of  

180
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:04,960
the ship's dining room. The man, Eddie saw, now 
turned to watch the dining room and the dancing.  

181
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:13,760
He was hidden in a fog of his own cigar smoke. How 
Eddie had hated him. And how, after all this time,  

182
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:16,560
he still hated him.
The memories. 

183
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:19,120
The anger.
The pain. 

184
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:24,640
"Are you sure you're feeling 
all right, Eddie?" asked Lynn  

185
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:29,200
when they got back to their cabin. Eddie 
was sitting on the bed staring into space. 

186
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:35,760
"Yes. Just tired. I think I'm still jet-lagged, 
and I'm tired after walking on the island today." 

187
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:37,920
"You sure?"
"Yes." 

188
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:42,560
"That trip on the glass-bottomed 
submarine was amazing, wasn't it?" 

189
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:47,040
"Yeah," said Eddie. But he 
still couldn't think straight.  

190
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:52,880
His mind was filling up more and more with the 
terrible realization that Dominic was on the ship. 

191
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:59,120
Lynn knew him too well. "Eddie," 
she said, sitting down beside him,  

192
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:04,080
taking his hand and looking at him. She 
stroked the back of his head. "What's wrong?" 

193
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:11,280
Eddie had decided to accept that the trip was 
now spoiled. Did he need to spoil it for his  

194
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:17,360
wife? She didn't have to know. They would have 
their luxury cruise and go home to a new life.  

195
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:23,360
The ship was big enough. Dominic and Eddie 
both looked older and Dominic probably wouldn't  

196
00:18:23,360 --> 00:18:29,040
even remember him, so why worry about it?
But all the old feelings were there again,  

197
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:32,720
and Eddie could sense his energy 
slipping away just thinking about it.  

198
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:39,200
It showed on his face and Lynn could see it. 
Eddie could never hide much from his wife,  

199
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:47,680
and before he knew it he found himself weakening.
"It's Dominic. He's on the ship." It sounded so  

200
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:51,760
strange to Eddie to even say those words.
There was a pause. 

201
00:18:52,800 --> 00:19:00,080
Lynn looked more closely at her husband.
"What?" said Lynn quietly. "Dominic Stephens?  

202
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:05,840
You're kidding."
"I'm not kidding, Lynn. I wish I was," said Eddie. 

203
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:10,000
"I haven't heard that name in a long time." 

204
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:13,440
"Well, he's here."
"How do you know he's here?" 

205
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:18,000
"I saw him. He was sitting at the bar this 
evening when we came in from the deck." 

206
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:23,440
"Eddie, we were sitting on the other side of 
the dining room - you could hardly see anything.  

207
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:27,840
How can you be sure it was him?"
"Oh, I'm sure, Lynn. No mistake.  

208
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:35,680
The same fat, lazy bloke. But less 
hair now. And grey. And fatter." 

209
00:19:37,120 --> 00:19:42,000
Lynn was still trying to take it in. 
"Dominic Stephens is on this ship?" 

210
00:19:43,040 --> 00:19:47,280
"Yes."
She waited a moment. "Oh, Eddie." 

211
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:54,320
They both sat there for a moment. Then Lynn 
spoke again. She was already recovering.  

212
00:19:55,280 --> 00:20:02,080
"Well, look, it's a long time ago, Ed. It doesn't 
matter any more. He doesn't matter any more. He's  

213
00:20:02,080 --> 00:20:06,160
nothing. You don't have to talk to him."
"I know." 

214
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:11,040
"It's a big ship," Lynn continued. "It's 
extremely unlikely you're going meet him..." 

215
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:15,680
"I saw him at the bar!" said Eddie.
"... and even if you met him by chance,  

216
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:21,600
as I said, he won't remember you." Then she 
looked closely at Eddie and asked softly,  

217
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:26,880
"You didn't speak to him, did you?"
"No," replied Eddie. "Of course not." 

218
00:20:27,920 --> 00:20:29,040
"And did he see you?" 

219
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:34,640
"No." Eddie wasn't sure if Dominic 
had seen him or not. Probably not.  

220
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:40,320
"Well, that's OK then," Lynn said, but 
she knew it was an unhelpful thing to say. 

221
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:46,320
"It's not OK, Lynn. It's not 
OK at all. That man is back." 

222
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:51,520
"He's not back. Try to calm down."
"Calm down?!" said Eddie,  

223
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:57,760
raising his voice and standing up. "We lost 
everything because of him, Lynn, everything - he  

224
00:20:57,760 --> 00:21:03,920
cheated and bullied and took it all away!"
"Yes, I know, Ed, but it was sixteen years ago.  

225
00:21:04,560 --> 00:21:10,640
We've come a long way since then. You and Clive 
have each just put ten million quid in the bank!" 

226
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:14,480
"So what? Dominic got away 
with it all at Fenton's!" 

227
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:22,000
"It's all in the past. It doesn't matter anymore."
"It does matter. He's still getting away with it.  

228
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:26,400
He still looks very pleased with himself."
"You don't know that.  

229
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:32,320
You don't know his life now. I can't believe 
we're talking about all this after so long." 

230
00:21:32,320 --> 00:21:36,640
"Because he's here, Lynn. 
On the ship. On our cruise!" 

231
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:45,120
"Eddie, listen to me. Calm down. He and Neal 
gave you a bad time, I know. But you fought back  

232
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:51,680
and survived, and you became successful anyway. 
Without him. In spite of him and the things he  

233
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:58,480
said and did. You're here with me now, on holiday, 
with financial security for the rest of our lives.  

234
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:05,280
You did it. You climbed back out of the hole 
and it's OK. He can't hurt you anymore." 

235
00:22:06,160 --> 00:22:11,840
"He nearly destroyed us, Lynn."
"But he didn't, did he? We didn't let him." 

236
00:22:12,560 --> 00:22:20,720
Eddie wiped the tears from his eyes. "I can't 
believe he's on board! Why? He's still out  

237
00:22:20,720 --> 00:22:28,240
there getting in the way. Spoiling everything."
"He's not spoiling anything. Only if you let him.  

238
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:36,240
You've come a long way since he pushed you out."
"So why do I suddenly feel so angry? I can't  

239
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:40,640
believe it. I think of him and those 
days at Fenton's from time to time,  

240
00:22:40,640 --> 00:22:46,800
sometimes a lot, and it never upsets me.
"Well, you went through a tough time.  

241
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:52,400
It was very hard. If you really did see him 
tonight, of course that's going to upset you.  

242
00:22:53,040 --> 00:23:00,000
It's not the same as the occasional memory."
"Oh, I saw him all right. He still smokes those  

243
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:03,200
hideous cigars."
"OK," said Lynn. 

244
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:07,520
"You went through it too, 
you know," he reminded her. 

245
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:10,000
"I know."
Another pause. 

246
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:19,360
"We lost so much, Lynn: the house, the money. 
Us. I was off sick for a year. A year!" 

247
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:26,320
"I know," said Lynn. "There's no getting away 
from the damage the man caused. But you have  

248
00:23:26,320 --> 00:23:32,720
to calm down. Nothing is going to happen. You 
don't have to see him again or talk to him." 

249
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:38,240
"Well, what if he takes the same excursion as us 
at some point? Or sits at our table for dinner?" 

250
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:43,360
"Eddie, there are almost 2,000 
people on board. It won't happen.  

251
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:50,160
We can ignore him. Being the sort of person 
Dominic is, he's probably treated lots of  

252
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:54,960
people the way he treated you, so he won't 
know who you are or remember what he did." 

253
00:23:56,000 --> 00:24:01,520
"Somehow that makes it worse."
"Well, there's nothing we can do about it. If  

254
00:24:01,520 --> 00:24:07,120
we see him again or he even recognizes you, we'll 
cross that bridge when we come to it, all right?" 

255
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:10,880
Eddie was quiet.
"All right?"  

256
00:24:11,760 --> 00:24:14,560
Lynn repeated, holding his face in her hands. 

257
00:24:15,760 --> 00:24:19,200
"OK," said Eddie.
 
 
CHAPTER FOUR

258
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:20,880
After the argument

259
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:28,560
Eddie sat in a cafe not far from the office, 
dipping his teaspoon into a large cappuccino,  

260
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:33,680
and tried to think of what he could do about 
his job. He could leave, but that would mean  

261
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:39,760
giving in and letting Dominic have exactly what 
he wanted. Besides, it would take several months,  

262
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:44,400
possibly a year, to find another good job, 
and he would still have to put up with him  

263
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:50,080
in the meantime. He could officially complain 
about Dominic's behavior. He had a strong case.  

264
00:24:50,720 --> 00:24:56,720
But that would only make things worse. Somehow 
Dominic had Gary, the CEO, on his side.  

265
00:24:57,280 --> 00:25:01,680
And Ann Blake, the Financial Director, 
would never support getting rid of Dominic,  

266
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:08,240
since she had hired him in the first place.
"He's unbelievable. He actually said I was  

267
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:12,400
too hands-on," said Eddie, stabbing 
at his drink with his spoon. 

268
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:18,160
"Really?" said Clive, who had left the 
office and found Eddie sitting in the cafe. 

269
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:23,520
"Yes. He also said I wasn't a leader 
and that Moscow was his deal." 

270
00:25:24,240 --> 00:25:28,960
"You're joking," said Clive. 
He seemed genuinely surprised.  

271
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:31,440
"That deal was yours. Everyone knows that." 

272
00:25:32,320 --> 00:25:34,720
"Then he said my communication 
wasn't good enough." 

273
00:25:35,360 --> 00:25:42,480
"Eh? He can talk. He's got no people skills 
whatsoever. Anyway, he never reads his emails." 

274
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:46,880
"I know. I told him that. 
He says I should phone him,"  

275
00:25:48,240 --> 00:25:52,080
and Eddie laughed in disgust.
"He's never there!" 

276
00:25:53,120 --> 00:26:00,240
"Exactly! I said that too. It's pointless, Clive. 
He doesn't listen and he interrupts all the time.  

277
00:26:00,240 --> 00:26:03,840
He's so smug. He thinks he's 
right about everything." 

278
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:08,480
"At least you're not alone. Everyone 
has the same problem with him." 

279
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:13,360
"Well, what is his problem?"
"It's obvious. He's insecure." 

280
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:17,120
"Well, it's not obvious when you're 
sitting in a meeting with him." 

281
00:26:17,120 --> 00:26:23,120
"He's a bully in a shirt and tie. All bullies 
are insecure. Maybe his dad didn't show  

282
00:26:23,120 --> 00:26:28,640
him any love. Maybe his dad's worse!"
Eddie tried to smile as he looked out  

283
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:34,320
of the window, as if the answer were out there 
somewhere. Maybe if he were to look long enough,  

284
00:26:34,320 --> 00:26:38,880
the answer would come and find him. 
He doubted it. He was exhausted. 

285
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:47,040
"Clive, how do they get to be in charge, these 
people? They're utterly useless. He's useless." 

286
00:26:47,760 --> 00:26:53,760
"Yes, and he knows it. Deep down. That's why 
he picks on people and moves responsibility.  

287
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:59,760
No one actually knows what he does."
"Yeah, and by the time they find out they  

288
00:26:59,760 --> 00:27:02,480
have to pay him a year's salary, 
and then he gets another job." 

289
00:27:03,120 --> 00:27:06,240
"That's his skill, though. He 
talks well to the top guys.  

290
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:11,840
But the real people don't respect him. I spoke 
to someone at Gallagher's the other week,  

291
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:15,040
where Dominic worked for about two 
years. They said the same thing." 

292
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:19,840
"Do you think he has any idea what 
people really think and say about him?" 

293
00:27:20,560 --> 00:27:27,280
"No, I don't think he does. He's so superior in 
his own mind he probably thinks we're all losers." 

294
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:34,560
"But he knows I'm good. He knows you're good 
too, and that really irritates him, because we  

295
00:27:34,560 --> 00:27:41,600
know this job and he doesn't. He just moves tasks 
and people around all day and calls it strategy." 

296
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:48,000
"I know," said Clive.
They both stared out of the window. 

297
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:53,520
"Did you hear what he said to Steve the 
other day?" asked Clive. "No, what?" 

298
00:27:54,800 --> 00:27:58,160
"'Dominic told Steve that he 
got the top job because Ann  

299
00:27:58,160 --> 00:28:06,320
and Gary saw him as a wise ambassador.'"
"Wise? Ambassador? Ambassador for what?" 

300
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:11,680
"Who knows? He's in his own dream world."
"Did he really say that?" 

301
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:17,600
"Yes. And when Steve questioned it, Dominic 
then said he was older than anyone else anyway." 

302
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:22,480
"Unbelievable."
"Who knows what he thinks?  

303
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:28,080
He's not like us. I think that scares him."
"Where do these people come from?" 

304
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:35,040
"I don't know, mate, but they soon move 
on. We just have to hold on. Look on  

305
00:28:35,040 --> 00:28:42,560
the bright side - it couldn't get any worse."
But Eddie wasn't so sure. Eddie had the feeling  

306
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:46,320
that things were going to get a lot worse.
And he was right. 

307
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:53,920
Back at home, Eddie spent the evening trying to 
catch up on the work he'd missed that afternoon,  

308
00:28:53,920 --> 00:28:57,840
and looking at the many emails he 
had sent Dominic. It was a nightmare. 

309
00:28:59,120 --> 00:29:04,000
Again and again he considered walking away 
from the job, but it hurt him more simply to  

310
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:09,920
give up. Besides, he was enjoying the Moscow 
project, and he had done so much work for it.  

311
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:13,920
When he was in Moscow, he 
could get on with things. He  

312
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:19,280
loved Russia and he loved the people there. 
It was such a different world from the UK;  

313
00:29:20,320 --> 00:29:28,160
and the owners of Zariya, Dima and Tatiana, always 
made him feel so welcome. Over time Eddie had  

314
00:29:28,160 --> 00:29:32,720
had to explain to them some of the difficulties 
back in London, and they had been very helpful.  

315
00:29:33,760 --> 00:29:40,000
Eddie was reading one of Dima's emails and 
smiling again when Lynn walked into the room. 

316
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:45,840
"Will you be much longer?" asked Lynn.
"Maybe. I'm behind on some deadlines,  

317
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:51,440
and today's battle with Dominic didn't help."
"Just leave it now, Ed. Come to bed," said Lynn. 

318
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:57,680
"I can't. There's so much. Too much."
"There's always too much,"  

319
00:29:57,680 --> 00:30:01,840
Lynn replied. "It will still be there 
in the morning. Give yourself a break." 

320
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:08,320
"Yeah, well, that's true, but with Dominic I have 
to be extra careful. He picks on everything." 

321
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:11,680
"He's an idiot."
"Yeah, I know it,  

322
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:15,440
and you know it, and everyone else 
knows it, but he's still the boss." 

323
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:22,640
"Well, what I mean is just ignore him."
"How can I ignore him, Lynn? He's the boss!  

324
00:30:22,640 --> 00:30:27,760
He runs the division. He runs me."
"Well, don't let him," said Lynn. 

325
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:33,120
"I'm not letting him!" shouted Eddie. "I'm 
trying to stop him. That's the problem!" 

326
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:38,960
"There's no need to shout, Eddie. I'm not deaf."
"Well, you're not being very helpful." 

327
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:43,760
"Thanks a lot," she said 
sarcastically. "I'm doing my best." 

328
00:30:44,800 --> 00:30:51,280
"Sorry. I was hired to build a team, win a project 
like the one in Moscow and make things profitable.  

329
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:57,280
He was brought in to oversee the whole division. 
Then he gets bonuses for doing very little,  

330
00:30:57,280 --> 00:31:00,240
and I get the blame when the 
numbers suddenly don't add up." 

331
00:31:00,960 --> 00:31:04,160
"Your numbers are fine."
"Not according to Dominic." 

332
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:07,680
"Why?"
"Oh, well, during our  

333
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:13,600
useless meeting today, he brought up that old 
story about being 25,000 pounds over budget,  

334
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:18,720
when everyone knows he fixed the numbers. 
Somehow he gets his bonuses and puts  

335
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:23,120
any blame on me. I'm almost certain 
now that he wants me out, Lynn." 

336
00:31:23,920 --> 00:31:31,360
"Surely not. He needs you. If it weren't for you, 
good people would have left ages ago. Besides,  

337
00:31:31,360 --> 00:31:35,120
who else could move Russia along?"
"Oh, don't mention Russia." 

338
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:41,680
"Why? That's your big success story."
"Oh, he keeps going on about the fact that  

339
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:46,960
he won the Moscow contract, not me."
"What? That's just not true." 

340
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:50,800
"I know."
"What about Ann and Gary?  

341
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:56,640
Can't you talk to them about all this?"
"They've changed, Lynn. I've hardly seen them  

342
00:31:56,640 --> 00:32:02,000
since the new partners came in. Besides, Gary and 
Dominic are always playing golf at the weekends.  

343
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:07,920
Ann's OK still, but she's very political, 
and I think she's embarrassed that Dominic's  

344
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:12,000
upsetting everyone. After all, she 
was the one who recruited him." 

345
00:32:12,960 --> 00:32:15,920
'And Human Resources? Can't 
you report him to them?" 

346
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:20,080
"What do I tell them? That he's 
got the people skills of a goat!" 

347
00:32:20,800 --> 00:32:25,600
"Well, that's one thing. And the 
intimidation, the lies and the..."  

348
00:32:25,600 --> 00:32:29,040
It's very hard to prove, Lynn. 
He's got his back covered,  

349
00:32:29,040 --> 00:32:32,640
and they would only report the whole 
thing to Ann and Gary. And then what?" 

350
00:32:33,280 --> 00:32:37,840
"Well, presumably they tell Dominic and 
you all get together and sort it out." 

351
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:44,160
"Easy, really. Why didn't I think of that?"
"You know what I mean, Eddie. There's no  

352
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:49,200
need to be sarcastic. I'm only trying to 
help. I hate it when you're like this." 

353
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:54,560
"Well, you're not living in the real world, 
are you, Lynn? You're a Primary school teacher,  

354
00:32:54,560 --> 00:32:59,280
for goodness' sake. If things go wrong, you 
all get into a circle and sing a song about  

355
00:32:59,280 --> 00:33:04,160
it. Or draw a picture. It's not that simple when 
you're in a multi-million pound business and..." 

356
00:33:05,280 --> 00:33:10,080
But Lynn had heard enough.
She was already leaving the room.  

357
00:33:10,080 --> 00:33:15,040
Eddie stared back at the open screen on 
his laptop at hundreds and hundreds of  

358
00:33:15,040 --> 00:33:19,840
emails. He thought about how much more 
he had to do before he could go to bed,  

359
00:33:20,560 --> 00:33:26,080
about the hurt he had caused Lynn and about the 
injustice of Dominic and of people like him. 

360
00:33:27,040 --> 00:33:32,880
Eddie slammed down the laptop lid.
The job was broken, the evening was broken,  

361
00:33:33,520 --> 00:33:38,000
and now his relationship was broken.
 
 
CHAPTER FIVE

362
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:38,800
Eddie's dream

363
00:33:40,480 --> 00:33:43,440
Although the sea was calm, 
Eddie didn't sleep well.  

364
00:33:44,080 --> 00:33:49,840
He had a dream that seemed to last all night.
It began with him lying in bed in the cabin of  

365
00:33:49,840 --> 00:33:54,480
the ship, and waking up to find himself 
in his old bedroom from his childhood.  

366
00:33:55,200 --> 00:34:01,840
But the bedroom was on the ship. He sat up in 
the top bunk of some familiar bunk beds. In the  

367
00:34:01,840 --> 00:34:08,080
bottom bunk should have been his sister Ellen, 
but he knew his wife was the occupant now. The  

368
00:34:08,080 --> 00:34:13,680
bottom bunk was empty, however, and he saw water 
coming in quietly but rapidly under the door. 

369
00:34:15,200 --> 00:34:19,840
In his dream, he jumped out of his bunk 
and straight into half a meter of water.  

370
00:34:20,560 --> 00:34:28,240
It was ice-cold and Eddie gasped in shock. He was 
wearing a grey suit and black shoes, but no socks,  

371
00:34:28,240 --> 00:34:34,880
shirt or tie. With his feet already going numb 
in the cold water, he opened the small wardrobe  

372
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:41,760
to look for them and found a public telephone. 
Business cards were stuck all over the wall. He  

373
00:34:41,760 --> 00:34:48,160
noticed his own from years ago with the familiar 
Fentons logo. But his details were in Russian. 

374
00:34:48,160 --> 00:34:50,880
His stomach was tight.
His head ached. 

375
00:34:51,600 --> 00:34:56,800
In his dreaming mind, a thousand tasks and 
deadlines seemed to weigh upon his shoulders. 

376
00:34:57,360 --> 00:35:03,520
The phone started ringing. He picked it up.
"Where are you?" a voice shouted on the other end. 

377
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:06,080
It was Dominic.
"The unmistakable,  

378
00:35:06,080 --> 00:35:09,760
cold, demanding tone of voice: 
"Do you know what time it is?" 

379
00:35:10,800 --> 00:35:16,960
Eddie lifted the sleeve of his suit to look at his 
watch, but its face was frosted over and unclear.  

380
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:20,400
Water had got into it somehow. 
The hands were barely visible. 

381
00:35:21,280 --> 00:35:26,000
"I can't tell," he heard himself say.
"You can't tell the time?  

382
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:29,920
Typical! What's the matter with you? 
We're all waiting for you. Come on." 

383
00:35:31,040 --> 00:35:35,600
"Who's waiting for me? Where are you?"
Eddie heard laughter in the background. 

384
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:40,160
"On the bridge. Where do you 
think?" Then the line went dead. 

385
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:47,440
The water was up to Eddie's knees now, and rising 
fast. He decided to leave the socks, shirt and  

386
00:35:47,440 --> 00:35:52,320
tie and make his way to the bridge - dressed 
or not dressed. How much worse could it be? 

387
00:35:53,360 --> 00:35:59,840
As Eddie opened the door, water poured in at waist 
level, and with it thousands of champagne glasses.  

388
00:36:00,640 --> 00:36:04,800
Most of them were intact, but many 
were broken. Too many for Eddie to  

389
00:36:04,800 --> 00:36:10,240
avoid. His chest and legs were cut many 
times as he waded out into the corridor. 

390
00:36:11,200 --> 00:36:17,200
He saw Clive at the far end.
"Clive!" he shouted. "Clive, it's me! Over here!" 

391
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:24,080
But Clive didn't hear him. He, too, was struggling 
with the strong current of water dragging him down  

392
00:36:24,080 --> 00:36:29,840
and away at the far end of the corridor.
"CLIVE!" shouted Eddie in his sleep. 

393
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:35,680
Opposite Eddie in the dream was a metal ladder 
which went up to the next level of the ship  

394
00:36:35,680 --> 00:36:42,320
through a small hole. It was big enough for him 
to get through. This ladder led to another ladder  

395
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:48,320
and another hole. And another. And another. 
Ladders stretched all the way in a giant tunnel  

396
00:36:48,320 --> 00:36:54,080
leading upwards. Eddie climbed and climbed. 
He could hear the laughter getting louder,  

397
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:58,880
so he decided to follow the sound.
When he reached the top, he suddenly  

398
00:36:58,880 --> 00:37:05,280
found himself on the ship's funnel. It was dark, 
and a strong sea wind took his breath away.  

399
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:11,520
He was scared and excited at the same time. He 
thought the funnel would be hot, but it was not.  

400
00:37:12,320 --> 00:37:17,520
It was at an angle, and he was looking up into 
the sky, almost touching the stars themselves. 

401
00:37:18,560 --> 00:37:23,440
"They're stars, Lynn. Not lights. 
You were wrong," he shouted again  

402
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:29,040
(in reality, his shouting woke Lynn up).
Then he looked around and saw that the  

403
00:37:29,040 --> 00:37:32,560
front part of the ship was already 
underwater and the ship was sinking. 

404
00:37:33,120 --> 00:37:39,840
"Lynn!" he shouted. This time it was a scream. 
That was when he slipped and fell and, in his  

405
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:47,120
sleep, flung out his arms to save himself. But 
there was no impact. Instead he was now standing  

406
00:37:47,120 --> 00:37:51,680
on the bridge of the ship, which was full of 
people from work - from his days at Fenton's.  

407
00:37:52,320 --> 00:37:57,040
People he hadn't thought of in all this time. 
People he thought he'd never remember again.  

408
00:37:57,760 --> 00:38:00,160
People he certainly didn't want to see again. 

409
00:38:01,120 --> 00:38:06,320
Ann and Gary were there, but they were behind 
Dominic, who stood by the wheel in his captain's  

410
00:38:06,320 --> 00:38:12,480
uniform staring at him. He was older now and 
heavier. The way Eddie had seen him at the bar. 

411
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:16,560
"Glad you could join us. 
We're only sinking, you know!" 

412
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:22,880
"What's going on?" said Eddie, looking around. 
The jazz band was playing in the corner,  

413
00:38:22,880 --> 00:38:28,480
but the female singer was not the girl he had seen 
earlier. Instead it was Lynn. Singing a song whose  

414
00:38:28,480 --> 00:38:30,320
name escaped him.
"Lynn?" 

415
00:38:31,440 --> 00:38:34,320
She didn't look at him. She 
was looking away and singing. 

416
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:41,840
"LYNN! What are you doing here?" 
shouted Eddie, confused and frightened. 

417
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:46,560
"I'm the captain. What does 
it look like?" said Dominic. 

418
00:38:46,560 --> 00:38:52,720
"No. Not you. Lynn. What's she doing 
here?" She wasn't paying him any attention. 

419
00:38:53,600 --> 00:38:58,240
More and more people were coming on to 
the bridge. He saw Dima and Tatiana.  

420
00:38:58,240 --> 00:39:02,560
They spoke in Russian. Eddie couldn't 
hear them over the laughter of the crowd. 

421
00:39:02,560 --> 00:39:07,040
"Ssh. I can't hear what they're saying. 
And I can't remember the name of the song." 

422
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:10,880
"Never mind that, Eddie. We've 
got more important things to do." 

423
00:39:11,520 --> 00:39:12,960
"What?"
Laughter. 

424
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:17,600
"We're sinking, no thanks to you."
"Why? What have I done?" 

425
00:39:18,160 --> 00:39:22,000
More laughter from the crowd.
A familiar face appeared. It was Neal. 

426
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:24,560
"Champagne glasses, Eddie.  

427
00:39:24,560 --> 00:39:27,840
Champagne glasses," he said.
"What about them?" 

428
00:39:28,560 --> 00:39:33,600
What about them?" shouted Dominic. 
"They put a hole in the ship, you fool." 

429
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:38,640
"That's impossible." Fear 
filled Eddie's mind and body. 

430
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:45,760
"Oh, really? Take a look around. Glass 
everywhere. Holes in the side of my ship." 

431
00:39:45,760 --> 00:39:52,080
"It's not your ship!" protested Eddie.
"Who cares? We'll be underwater in ten minutes.  

432
00:39:52,080 --> 00:39:56,160
Fifteen at the most," added Neal.
"Shut up, Neal. You're only  

433
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:59,840
here because of Dominic."
Then he heard a loud buzzing. 

434
00:40:00,480 --> 00:40:07,840
A giant helicopter arrived and flew over the front 
decks. And another. Three, four, five. Dozens.  

435
00:40:07,840 --> 00:40:14,000
Like bees around a beehive. Buzzing, louder 
and louder. They flew around and shone powerful  

436
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:20,880
lights on to the bridge. So many lights. The 
noise and lights were unbearable. Then sirens.  

437
00:40:20,880 --> 00:40:27,960
Police sirens. People screaming. Eddie covered 
his ears and shut his eyes. He cried out: "LYNN!" 

438
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:33,280
The noise lessened but the 
lights were bright, so bright.  

439
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:38,160
He was trying to open his eyes, but he 
couldn't. Now someone was pulling at his arms. 

440
00:40:38,160 --> 00:40:44,080
"Let me go! Let me go!" he shouted.
"Eddie..." Lynn said, trying to wake him up. 

441
00:40:44,800 --> 00:40:52,560
"Lynn?" His eyes were opening. It was so bright.
"It's all right, I'm here," she said, holding him. 

442
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:57,840
"We've got to get off! We're sinking!"
"It's all right," she said again. 

443
00:40:59,040 --> 00:41:04,160
Then his eyes opened and he was finally awake.
 
 
CHAPTER SIX

444
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:05,840
Another bad meeting

445
00:41:07,760 --> 00:41:13,360
The next morning Eddie woke early and his mind 
was racing. The house was quiet and there was  

446
00:41:13,360 --> 00:41:19,840
little traffic outside. He felt like he hadn't 
been to sleep at all, and he was still angry. 

447
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:26,400
Lynn was still asleep. It was 5.50 a.m. He 
listened to the radio for a while until he heard  

448
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:34,480
the news, and then he got up, had a shower and 
got dressed. By 6.45 a.m. he was ready for work  

449
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:39,440
and quickly said goodbye to Lynn before walking to 
the station to get the train into central London. 

450
00:41:40,960 --> 00:41:44,320
The train was full, but Eddie 
managed to get a seat by the window.  

451
00:41:45,040 --> 00:41:48,240
It was a fast train with only a 
couple of stops before Paddington.  

452
00:41:49,920 --> 00:41:54,400
As the train picked up speed and aimed for 
the city, Eddie looked out at the fields  

453
00:41:54,400 --> 00:42:01,200
and industrial estates passing by. He took deep 
breaths and tried to calm himself before the day  

454
00:42:01,200 --> 00:42:07,600
started. He thought about his conference call 
with Moscow at 9.30 a.m., his scheduled sales  

455
00:42:07,600 --> 00:42:14,640
meeting at 12 noon, and a lunch appointment at 
1.30 p.m. with Neal Skinner in Production. Then  

456
00:42:14,640 --> 00:42:19,680
he was hoping to block off a couple of hours in 
the afternoon to catch up on emails and paperwork. 

457
00:42:20,880 --> 00:42:26,480
He got to the office at 8.15 a.m. and sat at 
his desk with a double espresso and a bagel.  

458
00:42:27,520 --> 00:42:33,040
As his PC started up, Eddie sorted through some 
of his papers and wrote a quick to do list for  

459
00:42:33,040 --> 00:42:40,240
the day ahead. He logged on to his email and took 
care of a few basic queries, before noticing that  

460
00:42:40,240 --> 00:42:46,880
Dominic had sent a meeting schedule for 10 a.m. 
There was no subject heading. Eddie saw that it  

461
00:42:46,880 --> 00:42:52,240
clashed with his Moscow call, so he rejected 
it and suggested rescheduling for 11 a.m.,  

462
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:58,080
and wrote a line to ask what the meeting was 
about. To support his message, he mentioned  

463
00:42:58,080 --> 00:43:03,600
that he had an important call at 9.30 a.m. and 
asked Dominic for his patience in the matter.  

464
00:43:04,400 --> 00:43:09,440
It annoyed him to think that his day with 
Dominic was already starting on a negative note,  

465
00:43:09,440 --> 00:43:16,320
but he tried to put it to the back of his mind.
By 9 a.m. the open-plan office was filling up, and  

466
00:43:16,320 --> 00:43:22,320
Maxine, Paula and Gavin arrived, who all worked in 
Eddie's department and sat near him in the office. 

467
00:43:22,320 --> 00:43:26,800
"Hi, Ed! How's it going?" asked Paula.
"Fine, thanks," replied Eddie. 

468
00:43:27,520 --> 00:43:33,600
"How was the meeting with Dominic yesterday?" 
asked Gavin. "Oh, well, you know. A challenge,  

469
00:43:33,600 --> 00:43:38,080
shall we say," said Eddie, trying 
to smile and not give too much away. 

470
00:43:38,080 --> 00:43:43,840
"I bet it was. Rather you than me, mate," 
said Gavin. Eddie knew that Gavin and the  

471
00:43:43,840 --> 00:43:49,200
team were on his side, but what could they do?
Eddie went back to dealing with his emails and  

472
00:43:49,200 --> 00:43:56,160
preparing for the call to Moscow at 9.30 a.m.
At 9.20 a.m. his phone rang. It was Dominic.  

473
00:43:56,960 --> 00:44:00,240
"Did you get the meeting schedule 
I sent? 10 a.m. this morning." 

474
00:44:01,040 --> 00:44:07,440
"Yes, I replied. I can't do that time. I've got 
a call at 9.30 with Dima and his team in Moscow.  

475
00:44:07,440 --> 00:44:12,800
I'm dialing in Adam in IT, who needs an update on 
the platform they're using for the new software." 

476
00:44:13,520 --> 00:44:17,040
"It's too early for IT. Why are 
you bothering them with this?" 

477
00:44:17,680 --> 00:44:21,920
"Because we need their input on..."
"Look, Eddie. Forget IT and forget  

478
00:44:21,920 --> 00:44:26,640
your call. Do it tomorrow."
"I can't. It's taken ages to  

479
00:44:26,640 --> 00:44:30,880
find a time when we can all..."
"You and I have a meeting at 10." 

480
00:44:30,880 --> 00:44:36,080
"What about?"
"Let's discuss that then. OK?" Dominic hung up. 

481
00:44:37,280 --> 00:44:40,720
Eddie glanced around and 
noticed Maxine looking at him. 

482
00:44:40,720 --> 00:44:45,360
"You OK?" she asked.
"Not really. Max,  

483
00:44:45,360 --> 00:44:50,320
can you get hold of Dima for me and ask if he can 
reschedule the call for any time this afternoon?" 

484
00:44:51,040 --> 00:44:56,160
"He won't like it," she said.
"I know. Tell him I'm really sorry,  

485
00:44:56,160 --> 00:45:01,600
and tell him Dominic has to see me at 10 a.m. Tell 
him I didn't have any warning. He'll understand."  

486
00:45:02,400 --> 00:45:08,000
Eddie tried to smile again. This smile was more 
fake than the last, and Maxine could see it. 

487
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:12,480
"OK," she said.
Eddie calmly got up out  

488
00:45:12,480 --> 00:45:17,760
of his seat and walked across to the far side 
of the office floor, took the lift upstairs  

489
00:45:17,760 --> 00:45:23,840
and went into the gents' toilet. It was empty.
He went to the sink, turned on the cold tap,  

490
00:45:23,840 --> 00:45:28,240
collected water in his cupped hands and 
splashed it on his face to freshen up.  

491
00:45:29,280 --> 00:45:34,320
The situation was impossible, he thought. 
Eddie felt he could no longer do his job. 

492
00:45:36,320 --> 00:45:39,920
For a moment or two he stayed where 
he was, leaning over the sink,  

493
00:45:39,920 --> 00:45:45,360
staring at the pouring water and watching 
it go down the plughole. Then he looked up,  

494
00:45:45,360 --> 00:45:50,400
reached for some towels and dried his face.
At that moment the phone in his pocket  

495
00:45:50,400 --> 00:45:55,120
announced the arrival of a text with the 
sound of a mystical harp. It was from Lynn.
 

496
00:45:56,400 --> 00:46:01,040
sorry about last night, hope 
u r ok. stay strong. D is a  

497
00:46:01,040 --> 00:46:09,120
useless robot and he knows it. love u. L. x
 
Eddie smiled and punched back a quick reply: 

498
00:46:09,920 --> 00:46:15,600
thanks, love u 2. X
 
The text and cold water  

499
00:46:15,600 --> 00:46:19,200
seemed to give Eddie enough strength to go 
back and face another meeting with Dominic.  

500
00:46:20,000 --> 00:46:25,520
It was almost ten o'clock. He had enough time to 
grab a coffee before going to Dominic's office. 

501
00:46:27,120 --> 00:46:32,640
Eddie knocked on the door, walked in and sat 
down. Dominic was engrossed in something on his  

502
00:46:32,640 --> 00:46:39,280
PC. Without looking up he muttered, "I'll be with 
you in a moment," and spent the next five minutes  

503
00:46:39,280 --> 00:46:44,960
doing more work and ignoring Eddie. He even made 
a phone call to someone Eddie had never heard of.  

504
00:46:45,920 --> 00:46:50,480
Eventually, Dominic turned his attention 
away from his computer and on to Eddie. 

505
00:46:51,040 --> 00:46:53,360
"Right. What's the latest from Moscow?" 

506
00:46:54,160 --> 00:46:58,880
"I haven't called them yet."
"Why not?" Dominic's tone was sharp.  

507
00:46:58,880 --> 00:47:04,960
Eddie was always amazed at how unpleasant and cold 
this man was. Was he like this at home? What kind  

508
00:47:04,960 --> 00:47:11,200
of friends did he have? Did he have any friends?
"I had a call planned for this morning at 9.30,  

509
00:47:11,200 --> 00:47:13,920
but you asked me to change it so 
that we could have this meeting." 

510
00:47:14,560 --> 00:47:18,560
"So when are you talking to them?"
"I don't know yet," said Eddie. 

511
00:47:18,560 --> 00:47:21,040
"You need to get a call 
sorted as soon as possible." 

512
00:47:21,760 --> 00:47:24,960
"Maxine's doing that now."
"Maxine shouldn't be doing  

513
00:47:24,960 --> 00:47:30,240
that sort of thing. She's only a temp."
"Well, she sometimes takes phone calls  

514
00:47:30,240 --> 00:47:36,320
for us in the office and sets UP meetings."
"She's not a secretary, Eddie, she's a student!  

515
00:47:36,320 --> 00:47:40,880
She types in data. You can't ask her 
to phone our biggest customers..." 

516
00:47:41,840 --> 00:47:46,160
Eddie's face was red, he could feel 
it. Already things were out of control. 

517
00:47:46,880 --> 00:47:50,240
"She's only setting up a 
conference call," he said. 

518
00:47:50,240 --> 00:47:56,960
"Do it yourself," said Dominic impatiently.
"Fine," Eddie. It wasn't fine at all. 

519
00:47:57,760 --> 00:48:01,200
"And copy me in on the schedule. 
I want to join the call." 

520
00:48:02,000 --> 00:48:03,920
"Why?"
"I want to find  

521
00:48:03,920 --> 00:48:08,000
out when Dima's going to order the rest of the 
software for all the offices in the region." 

522
00:48:08,880 --> 00:48:14,320
"Dominic, please leave that to me. This call 
is more for product training and looking at any  

523
00:48:14,320 --> 00:48:19,040
specific problems so far. I don't want 
to distract him with pressure for more  

524
00:48:19,040 --> 00:48:23,120
orders. We have time for that."
"We don't have time, Eddie." 

525
00:48:23,760 --> 00:48:29,520
"Yes, we do. At least until my next visit to 
Moscow. That's when we will be looking at the next  

526
00:48:29,520 --> 00:48:34,640
orders. As a matter of fact I've got a meeting 
with Neal in Production today to look at costs." 

527
00:48:35,920 --> 00:48:40,160
There was a knock on the door and Neal Skinner, 
Head of Production, walked into the office. 

528
00:48:41,120 --> 00:48:46,800
"Well, well. Here he is!" said Dominic. "Come 
in, Neal. We were just talking about you." 

529
00:48:47,680 --> 00:48:52,240
"Nothing bad, I hope," said 
Neal. His smile was insincere. 

530
00:48:53,200 --> 00:48:57,680
He was a very tall, thin man who 
always looked pale and wore dull suits.  

531
00:48:58,400 --> 00:49:04,000
The Grey Man, they called him in the office. 
Neal was Eddie's main contact in Production  

532
00:49:04,000 --> 00:49:06,240
for all things related to the Moscow project. 

533
00:49:07,200 --> 00:49:10,800
He was a cold character who 
took himself very seriously  

534
00:49:10,800 --> 00:49:16,640
and had little sense of humor. Like Dominic, 
he had a superior manner and was stubborn.  

535
00:49:18,000 --> 00:49:22,960
When engaged in conversation he looked at the 
other person critically, judging them negatively.  

536
00:49:23,840 --> 00:49:28,640
Neal always tried to give the impression that 
he knew everyone and that he was in charge,  

537
00:49:28,640 --> 00:49:33,520
but it was clear he was not really comfortable in 
his role and didn't really know what he was doing.  

538
00:49:34,720 --> 00:49:39,840
He hid behind business jargon, name-dropping 
and things he had learned from going on too many  

539
00:49:39,840 --> 00:49:46,400
training courses. But bosses liked him. Employees 
and customers did not. They thought he was a waste  

540
00:49:46,400 --> 00:49:52,400
of time. Eddie knew he was a waste of time.
"Neal, thanks for joining us." 

541
00:49:53,280 --> 00:49:58,400
"No problem," Neal replied. So 
agreeable. So good with a boss around.  

542
00:49:58,400 --> 00:50:04,320
Neal crossed his long legs and folded his arms.
Eddie now had a feeling that this meeting had been  

543
00:50:04,320 --> 00:50:09,680
arranged, and that Neal was part of it. It was no 
coincidence that he had turned up at that point. 

544
00:50:10,480 --> 00:50:14,960
"Did you see the match last night?" 
Neal asked Dominic. Still no smile. 

545
00:50:15,680 --> 00:50:20,080
"No, I missed it. I heard that new 
defender Slater scored an own goal  

546
00:50:20,080 --> 00:50:26,160
and saved us. That was very kind, thank you."
"We're still five points ahead of you, though." 

547
00:50:26,160 --> 00:50:30,880
"Not for long. You've got Chelsea on Saturday, and 
then you're away to Liverpool the following week." 

548
00:50:31,760 --> 00:50:37,040
"Gentlemen," interrupted Eddie, "if it's OK 
with you... could we get back to business?" 

549
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:43,440
"The thing is, Eddie," said Dominic, "we 
need more people on the Moscow account..." 

550
00:50:44,560 --> 00:50:48,960
Eddie wasn't sure where this was going, but he 
was slightly encouraged by the possibility of  

551
00:50:48,960 --> 00:50:53,840
getting more assistance. "Right. That's 
good," he said, trying to be positive.  

552
00:50:54,480 --> 00:50:57,680
"We're short-staffed, as you 
know, and we could use more help."  

553
00:50:58,640 --> 00:51:03,280
But he still wasn't sure why Neal was 
there - he remained still and quiet,  

