00:51:03,280 --> 00:51:09,600
looking first at Dominic and then at Eddie.
"... so Neal has agreed to take charge and  

555
00:51:09,600 --> 00:51:15,280
give you guys a hand." Dominic looked back at 
his computer screen, then tapped something on  

556
00:51:15,280 --> 00:51:19,840
his keyboard. Eddie looked at Neal.
"Take charge of what,  

557
00:51:19,840 --> 00:51:25,920
exactly?" he asked, looking back at Dominic.
"Take charge of the account. In Moscow."  

558
00:51:27,040 --> 00:51:32,160
Dominic gave a little laugh.
Eddie went cold. He could feel the sharp blade  

559
00:51:32,160 --> 00:51:39,040
of realization enter his back. "Are you moving 
to Moscow, Neal?" he asked, confused but hopeful. 

560
00:51:39,760 --> 00:51:44,960
"No, mate. I'm staying in London." 
Neal smiled his superior smile. 

561
00:51:46,000 --> 00:51:49,840
Eddie did not like the sound of this. 
He didn't like being laughed at either. 

562
00:51:50,800 --> 00:51:55,680
Eddie turned his attention to Dominic. "Dominic, 
I don't quite follow. What's going on?" 

563
00:51:56,400 --> 00:52:02,000
"I've decided to make some changes in the team. 
Neal has a lot of experience in this field, so  

564
00:52:02,000 --> 00:52:07,600
you will report to him. He is now Head of Product 
and Business Development. It's a new position." 

565
00:52:10,240 --> 00:52:15,440
Neal kept his eyes on Dominic the whole time. 
He looked very pleased with himself, as if he  

566
00:52:15,440 --> 00:52:20,800
was waiting to be given a trophy of some sort.
'It makes sense, Eddie. Really," said Neal. 

567
00:52:21,440 --> 00:52:26,000
"I'm not interested in your opinion," 
snapped Eddie. He was trying to stay calm  

568
00:52:26,000 --> 00:52:32,000
but inside he was ready to explode. He tried 
to keep his voice steady. He leaned forward  

569
00:52:32,000 --> 00:52:37,840
on Dominic's desk and looked him in the eye.
"So what's my position?" he asked.
 
 

