CHAPTER SEVEN

571
00:52:40,160 --> 00:52:41,840
An encounter in Barbados

572
00:52:43,520 --> 00:52:46,880
The Parvina docked quietly 
at Bridgetown, Barbados,  

573
00:52:46,880 --> 00:52:52,560
at 7.20 a.m. Eddie and Lynn were already 
awake and they lay in bed listening to  

574
00:52:52,560 --> 00:53:00,160
the radio. At 7.30 there was a knock on the door.
"Good morning. Breakfast," said the voice outside. 

575
00:53:00,160 --> 00:53:04,560
Eddie got out of bed, almost believing 
he would step into cold water once more,  

576
00:53:04,560 --> 00:53:11,040
and opened the door. A young, smiling man brought 
in a large tray full of cereals, orange juice,  

577
00:53:11,040 --> 00:53:16,880
pastries and a cafeteria of coffee. Eddie led him 
through the cabin to the balcony door, which he  

578
00:53:16,880 --> 00:53:24,080
opened. The humid air struck him immediately.
"Phew, it's warm. Leave the tray inside," he  

579
00:53:24,080 --> 00:53:29,200
said to the man. "Thanks." Eddie gave 
him a few dollars and the man left. 

580
00:53:30,800 --> 00:53:34,880
Eddie looked out across the harbour 
view to where blue sea met white sand,  

581
00:53:34,880 --> 00:53:40,960
to the houses dotted about the town, and to 
the green palm trees inland. Market stalls were  

582
00:53:40,960 --> 00:53:46,000
already being set up near the ship, where locals 
could sell souvenirs and fruit to the passengers.  

583
00:53:47,120 --> 00:53:52,880
Eddie heard the distinctive metallic sound of a 
steel band and saw five boys playing down below.  

584
00:53:54,160 --> 00:53:58,400
He could see at least three other ships 
in the harbour. Given his nightmare,  

585
00:53:58,400 --> 00:54:01,680
he really appreciated the fact 
that this was the reality. 

586
00:54:03,120 --> 00:54:06,800
"Good morning, Mrs Millionaire. 
Another day in paradise," he said. 

587
00:54:08,560 --> 00:54:13,360
"What's for breakfast?" asked Lynn, yawning.
"Get up and have a look." 

588
00:54:14,320 --> 00:54:19,600
"You seem very awake and lively," she said.
"Yes, well, after last night's trip  

589
00:54:19,600 --> 00:54:24,800
to hell and back, this comes as a relief."
"You were in a terrible state. Do you remember?" 

590
00:54:25,600 --> 00:54:31,280
"Yes. I'm trying not to think about it," said 
Eddie. And he really was trying not to think about  

591
00:54:31,280 --> 00:54:37,680
it - about the dream, about Dominic Stephens, 
about the real nightmare of sixteen years ago.  

592
00:54:37,680 --> 00:54:42,320
But he knew it wouldn't be easy.
"Damn him," he said under his breath. 

593
00:54:44,480 --> 00:54:49,840
Lynn and Eddie had decided to do different things 
that day. Eddie had chosen to go on a catamaran  

594
00:54:49,840 --> 00:54:55,760
and snorkeling trip in the morning, while Lynn 
had booked tennis lessons. They took a taxi to  

595
00:54:55,760 --> 00:55:00,560
the Tropical Beach Hotel and Spa, where they 
were welcomed with fruit punch and given a short  

596
00:55:00,560 --> 00:55:06,720
talk about the area by one of the hotel guides.
The catamaran was scheduled to depart from the  

597
00:55:06,720 --> 00:55:12,880
hotel's private beach at 10.30 a.m., and Eddie 
put on his life jacket and joined several other  

598
00:55:12,880 --> 00:55:19,360
passengers and hotel guests for the two-hour 
trip. He was given a mask, snorkel and fins,  

599
00:55:19,360 --> 00:55:24,640
and he waved to Lynn as he walked down to where 
the boat was tied up. He was carrying his deck  

600
00:55:24,640 --> 00:55:30,640
shoes and had a towel in his hand as he made 
his way, barefoot, across the fine, smooth sand. 

601
00:55:32,720 --> 00:55:37,920
As he waited his turn to get on board, he looked 
down at his feet in the warm, green water and  

602
00:55:37,920 --> 00:55:42,880
thought again about the nightmare and about 
Dominic. He wondered where Dominic was today.  

603
00:55:43,440 --> 00:55:49,760
Was he on a trip? Was he even still on board?
In the taxi on the way to the hotel,  

604
00:55:49,760 --> 00:55:52,560
Eddie had worried that Dominic 
would be on the same excursion.  

605
00:55:53,200 --> 00:55:58,240
But how likely was it that he would meet him? 
He started feeling angry again that Dominic was  

606
00:55:58,240 --> 00:56:04,800
on the ship. And that he still existed at all.
In spite of this, Eddie was able to relax during  

607
00:56:04,800 --> 00:56:11,040
the boat trip. After an hour of sailing around the 
bay and past some spectacular beaches and coves,  

608
00:56:11,040 --> 00:56:15,840
the catamaran dropped anchor and the small 
group went snorkeling near an old shipwreck.  

609
00:56:16,640 --> 00:56:21,120
They watched and fed some stingrays, and 
Eddie enjoyed the calming effect of being  

610
00:56:21,120 --> 00:56:27,280
below the surface and in a very different world 
underwater. He was a good swimmer and very fit.  

611
00:56:27,840 --> 00:56:32,640
He had swum for his school and his university, 
and he had won medals for long-distance swimming.  

612
00:56:33,360 --> 00:56:37,280
Even now, at home, he tried to get to 
the local pool at least twice a week. 

613
00:56:38,480 --> 00:56:42,560
When he got back to the beach hotel, 
he was feeling tired but refreshed.  

614
00:56:42,560 --> 00:56:48,400
He'd caught the sun too, and his forehead and 
nose were burnt. He found Lynn sitting on a sun  

615
00:56:48,400 --> 00:56:53,760
lounger by a small pool with fountains. She 
was reading and sipping another fruit punch. 

616
00:56:54,800 --> 00:56:58,240
"Hello, you. I thought I'd 
find you here," he said. 

617
00:56:58,240 --> 00:57:00,960
"Oh, hi. How was it?"
"Brilliant." 

618
00:57:02,000 --> 00:57:07,120
"You've caught the sun."
"I know. I forgot to take some decent sun block.  

619
00:57:07,120 --> 00:57:10,080
I borrowed some off the guys on the 
boat, but I think it was too late." 

620
00:57:10,960 --> 00:57:13,760
"Here," she said, reaching 
for some cream in her bag.  

621
00:57:14,880 --> 00:57:20,240
"Use some of this." She passed him a tube 
of cream and Eddie squeezed some into his  

622
00:57:20,240 --> 00:57:24,880
hand and rubbed it on his face.
"How was the tennis?" he asked. 

623
00:57:24,880 --> 00:57:28,960
"It was cancelled. The guy never turned up, 
and it was too late to get another trainer." 

624
00:57:29,840 --> 00:57:32,800
"Really? That's not good. 
We've already paid for it." 

625
00:57:33,440 --> 00:57:37,280
"I know," said Lynn, "but they're 
giving us lunch for free instead,  

626
00:57:37,280 --> 00:57:42,000
so I don't mind really. I'm booked for tennis 
again in St Lucia in a few days, so that's OK." 

627
00:57:42,720 --> 00:57:48,880
He mocked her: "Listen to you! I 'm booked 
for tennis again in St Lucia in a few days,  

628
00:57:48,880 --> 00:57:52,560
she says, sipping her cocktail." Then he said,  

629
00:57:52,560 --> 00:57:57,200
"This is the life, eh?"
"It certainly is. Oh, look, here's Jen." 

630
00:57:58,240 --> 00:58:02,480
"Who's Jen?" asked Eddie, looking 
around. He thought she looked familiar. 

631
00:58:03,120 --> 00:58:07,200
"She was booked for the tennis as well, so we 
came here for a drink instead and we started  

632
00:58:07,200 --> 00:58:12,080
chatting. You'll never guess who she is."
"I know her, don't I?" asked Eddie. 

633
00:58:12,800 --> 00:58:16,880
"Yes and no. The same thing happened 
to me when I first saw her." 

634
00:58:16,880 --> 00:58:22,080
"She's from the ship. She must be," he said. Jen 
was almost at the pool where they were sitting. 

635
00:58:23,360 --> 00:58:26,480
"Yes. Not only that. She's 
the singer in the band!" 

636
00:58:27,520 --> 00:58:33,760
"Oh yes!" said Eddie, turning to meet her. 
She had on wide sunglasses and a baseball cap.  

637
00:58:34,400 --> 00:58:38,720
She wore a colourful sarong with palm 
tree patterns, and her T-shirt was orange  

638
00:58:38,720 --> 00:58:44,160
with a black saxophone logo. She was carrying a 
drink in one hand and a cigarette in the other. 

639
00:58:45,200 --> 00:58:51,600
"Hi, Lynn. Is this your man then?" asked Jen.
"Yes, this is Eddie. Eddie, this is Jen." 

640
00:58:52,800 --> 00:58:55,600
"Nice to meet you, Jen," 
Eddie said, shaking her hand. 

641
00:58:56,640 --> 00:59:02,560
"Likewise," she said. "How was the boat trip?"
"Great, thanks. They took us around some  

642
00:59:02,560 --> 00:59:06,720
fabulous beaches. Then we stopped and 
swam off the reef near an old shipwreck." 

643
00:59:07,360 --> 00:59:11,040
"Cool!" said Jen.
"Some stingrays came by and  

644
00:59:11,040 --> 00:59:14,880
we were given some food for them."
"Oh, I'd love to do that,  

645
00:59:14,880 --> 00:59:19,680
but I'd be terrified," said Jen.
"They're not that dangerous actually,  

646
00:59:19,680 --> 00:59:23,360
although they can give you a nasty bite."
"Ugh!" said Lynn. 

647
00:59:23,920 --> 00:59:29,360
"Or sting with their tail," added Jen.
"Yeah, well, that's true. It's rare, though," said  

648
00:59:29,360 --> 00:59:34,160
Eddie. "That usually happens if you stand on one 
when they're buried in the sand in shallow water." 

649
00:59:35,040 --> 00:59:38,880
"Aren't you afraid of sharks?" asked 
Jen, lifting up her sunglasses. 

650
00:59:39,600 --> 00:59:42,640
"I try not to stand on 
sharks," said Eddie, smiling. 

651
00:59:43,280 --> 00:59:46,320
"You know what I mean."
"There weren't any in the  

652
00:59:46,320 --> 00:59:50,160
area we were in," said Eddie, sitting 
down on a sun lounger next to his wife. 

653
00:59:51,040 --> 00:59:55,040
"How do you know?" asked Lynn.
"Well, you don't. You have to  

654
00:59:55,040 --> 00:59:58,640
hope that there aren't any."
"You must be mad," said Jen. 

655
00:59:59,680 --> 01:00:03,360
"It's worth it. The fish you can 
see near the reef are so beautiful." 

656
01:00:04,240 --> 01:00:07,440
"Well, Jen and I have been doing as 
little as possible, haven't we, Jen?" 

657
01:00:08,000 --> 01:00:12,000
"Absolutely," said Jen, sitting back 
on her lounger and sipping her drink. 

658
01:00:13,120 --> 01:00:15,120
"So, no tennis, then?" asked Eddie. 

659
01:00:15,920 --> 01:00:19,520
"No," said Jen. "But we get 
a free lunch," she added. 

660
01:00:20,080 --> 01:00:22,720
"So I heard," said Eddie. 
"What are you doing later?" 

661
01:00:23,600 --> 01:00:28,080
"Well, my partner will be here soon and 
we're booked to go on the Island Safari." 

662
01:00:28,080 --> 01:00:33,120
"Oh, I saw that in the brochure," said Lynn. "Is 
that the trip where you get a private jeep and go  

663
01:00:33,120 --> 01:00:38,880
around the island and see the Wildlife Reserve?"
"Yes, that's it. I love all the animal trips.  

664
01:00:38,880 --> 01:00:44,240
I can't wait. Dominic isn't keen at all, but he 
says he doesn't mind as long as he gets his golf,  

665
01:00:45,200 --> 01:00:52,400
Typical! It's like he's married to the stupid 
game. I find it so dull. He loves it, though.  

666
01:00:52,400 --> 01:00:56,160
Do you play golf, Eddie?"
 
 
