1230
01:51:29,440 --> 01:51:33,920
The ship was so big and there were so 
many people, with so many things going on,  

1231
01:51:33,920 --> 01:51:39,200
that Dominic's disappearance seemed only a 
minor problem. It was almost like an additional  

1232
01:51:39,200 --> 01:51:45,120
activity for the passengers to talk about. 
Who was the man? When did he disappear? Why?  

1233
01:51:45,120 --> 01:51:49,440
What happened? Was he injured on the 
ship somewhere? Did he fall overboard? 

1234
01:51:51,280 --> 01:51:56,400
Eddie and Lynn walked into town to get away from 
things. They walked for hours around the streets  

1235
01:51:56,400 --> 01:52:01,200
and marinas. Here and there they stopped and 
looked at their map, and read their guidebook  

1236
01:52:01,200 --> 01:52:07,680
about the history of Bridgetown. They tried not 
to talk about Dominic, or even to think about it.  

1237
01:52:08,400 --> 01:52:12,240
But Eddie could see that Lynn was worried, 
and Lynn could see the same in Eddie.  

1238
01:52:13,200 --> 01:52:19,600
Sooner or later they had to talk again. So they 
had lunch in a cafe overlooking a small bay,  

1239
01:52:19,600 --> 01:52:23,680
